 Two suspects are expected in court on Tuesday following the brutal killing of a 25-year-old woman in Ngcobo over the weekend. "It is alleged that deceased was driving her vehicle at Caca A/A on her way. She got stuck and two men came pretending to give help to the lady," said police spokesperson,Â Captain Namhla Mdleleni. "They drew a 9 mm pistol shooting the lady with several shots. "Community members took the lady to All.Saints hospital where she later died." Captain Mdleleni said that two suspects, aged between 35 & 45 years, were arrested and firearms with live ammunition were also recovered. "Both suspects will appear before Ngcobo Magistrate's Court on Tuesday." 